The final list of winners for the aviation part of Travellers Awards was released Tuesday by the organisers. Travellers Awards, instituted in 1996 by the publishers of Travellers Magazine and Atqnews.com with the motto: “Promoting Excellence in Travels”, is the leading travel and tourism awards body in Nigeria. The awards will be presented on March 11, 2022, in Abuja. In the aviation category, Aviation Personality of the Year is Capt Musa Nuhu (DG of NCAA) for navigating the resumption of civil aviation in Nigeria and bringing it back to good health within 12 months. He is also credited for the deft handling of aeropolitics in 2021. Aviation CEO of the Year is Engr Akin Olateru (AIB’s commissioner and CEO). He is credited with clearing the backlog of accident investigations in the last 18 months. Under his watch the Accident Investigation Bureau (AIB) has grown and established itself as a relevant player in aviation in Nigeria and West Africa. In other categories, Aviation Company of the Year is Pathfinder, which has been working silently for seamless operations of international travels in Nigeria, while Aviation Handling Company of the Year is SAHCO PLC.